benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache/accounts/{accountId} - Invalidates Caches per account level

covered: Valid Deletion: Successful cache invalidation for an existing account (TC01) and backward-compatibility scenario (TC19) cover the core DELETE operation returning 204 and invalidating caches.
Non-Existent Resource: 404 responses for non-existent accounts (TC02) and edge cases with no accounts or partially populated DB (TC16, TC18).
Invalid accountId format: 400 responses for malformed/encoded accountId (TC03, TC12) and injection attempt (TC14).
Missing accountId in path: 404 for missing path parameter (TC04).
Authorization: 401 responses for unauthenticated or invalid tokens (TC05, TC06).
Query Parameters: Handling of extra query parameters (TC09).
Unsupported HTTP Methods: 405 for unsupported method (GET) on this endpoint (TC11).
Concurrency and resiliency: Concurrency (TC13) and degraded service or cache dependency (TC07, TC08) plus network recovery (TC17).
Security: SQL injection (TC14) and XSS (TC15) tests cover input validation to 400.
gaps: Soft Deletes: No tests for logical vs physical delete semantics (soft delete).
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting/throttling of DELETE requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or actual client caching behavior.
Comprehensive method coverage: Only GET has 405 coverage; no tests for PUT/POST/PATCH on this endpoint.
Additional malformed inputs: Some edge cases not explicitly covered beyond those listed (e.g., extremely long IDs or unusual encodings).
recommendations: Add tests to verify soft delete semantics and idempotence (e.g., multiple DELETE calls).
Add rate limiting tests to ensure resilience under burst traffic.
Add tests to verify caching headers and caching behavior on DELETE responses.
Add tests for other HTTP methods (PUT/POST/PATCH) to ensure 405 responses on this endpoint.
Expand edge-case input coverage (e.g., very long IDs, unusual encodings) and 422 responses for invalid payload fields.
